<dl class="enableFormTabbing"> <dt id="fieldsetlegend-Access"> Access </dt> <dd id="fieldset-Access">
<div style="margin-left:-20px;margin-bottom:30px;" class="center">
	<h2 style="margin-bottom:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #888;font-size:1.6em;text-align:left;">Bika 3 Gaob LIMS Workflow</h2>
	<p style="line-height:140%;font-size:1.2em;text-align:left;">Bika workflow has been designed to fit with all types of labs and is totally conformant with ISO-17025 accreditation. Also, Bika's flexibility and open-source approach allows you to customize the system according to your lab specific requirements.</p></br><img src="workflow-diagram.png" alt="Bika LIMS" class="image-inline" title="Bika LIMS">
</div>
<div style="margin-left:-20px;margin-bottom:30px;">
	<div style="float:left;width:47%;">
		<h2 style="margin-bottom:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #888;font-size:1.6em;">Why Gaob release name?</h2>
		<p style="line-height:140%;font-size:1.2em;">In the tradition of <i>Chief </i>Inkosi Bika LIMS 2 using a  title for a release, this edition is code-named<i> </i>Gaob Bika LIMS 3. Gaob, <i>King,</i> is taken from <a class="external-link" href="http://www.san.org.za/">Khoi San</a> Nama, language of <a class="external-link" href="http://www.independent.co.uk/news/science/worlds-most-ancient-race-traced-in-dna-study-1677113.html">the world's first  people</a>.</p>

		<h2 style="margin-bottom:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #888;font-size:1.6em;padding-top:15px;">Initial testing data</h2>
		<p style="line-height:140%;font-size:1.2em;">We created standardised spreadsheets to configure the LIMS with setup data of your choice. The demo is populated with data of uniform   nature for ease of testing. See <a href="setup-data-in-this-installation" class="internal-link">Setup data used to configure this installation</a></p>
	</div>

	<div style="float:right;width:47%;">
		<h2 style="margin-bottom:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #888;font-size:1.6em;">Bika 3 Gaob installation</h2>
		<p style="line-height:140%;font-size:1.2em;">Bika 3 Gaob can be installed easily in a ready-to-use way for <a href="http://www.bikalabs.com/helpcentre/manual/bika-installation-guides/bika-on-ubuntu-linux/installing-bika-lims-3">Linux</a> and <a href="http://www.bikalabs.com/helpcentre/manual/bika-installation-guides/bika-on-windows/installing-bika-lims-3-0">Windows</a>.</p>
		<p style="line-height:140%;font-size:1.2em;">
		If you want more power, you can also install Bika 3 Gaob by retrieving the source code directly from the repository, allowing easy system updates. That's the <span style="font-weight:bold;font-size:0.9em;color:#333">recommended installation method for developers and testing purposes</span>. You can find the instructions <a href="https://github.com/bikalabs/Bika-LIMS/blob/master/docs/installation.txt">here</a>.
		</p>
	</div>

	<div style="clear:both">
		<h2 style="margin-bottom:10px;padding-top:15px;border-bottom:1px solid #888;font-size:1.6em;">Feedback and support</h2>
		<ul style="font-size:1.2em;margin-left:15px;">
			<li>Bika mailing lists: <a class="external-link" href="https://groups.google.com/forum/?hl=en#%21forum/bika-design">LIMS design</a>, <a class="external-link" href="http://lists.sourceforge.net/lists/listinfo/bika-users">Users</a> or <a class="external-link" href="http://lists.sourceforge.net/lists/listinfo/bika-developers">Developers</a></li>
			<li>Bugs reporting, Issues and Feature requests: <a class="external-link" href="https://github.com/bikalabs/Bika-LIMS/issues">public issue tracker</a></li>
			<li>IRC: <a class="chatzilla-link" href="http://webchat.freenode.net?channels=bika" id="ch-url-anchor">irc://freenode/bika</a>, the #bika channel on irc.freenode.net</li>
		</ul>
	</div>
</div>
<div style="clear:both"></div>
</dd> <dt id="fieldsetlegend-New"> New functions</dt> <dd id="fieldset-New">
<table class="invisible two_column_table">
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>
<p align="center"><a class="external-link" href="http://www.bikalabs.com/portfolio/umhlathuze"><img alt="Umhlathuze logo" class="image-inline" src="http://www.bikalabs.com/images/umhlathuze" /></a></p>
<p>New items sponsored by the water quality lab at the City of uMhlathuze, Richards Bay:</p>
<a class="external-link" href="bika_setup/bika_calculations">Results calculations</a>,     including interim fields and dependent analyses, are user    configurable and new calculations can be added by authorised users<br /><br /> Dormant setup items can be de-activated, which will remove them from general view while maintaining database integrity. The same for sample and analysis request cancellation workflows<br /><br />
<p><a class="external-link" href="http://plone.org/">Plone 4</a>'s versioning is used to maintain references to historical data. Working copy support combined with  content locking  allow multiple users  access to data without conflicts</p>
<p>Using AJAX, Plone 4's user interface and a host of smaller enhancements, many clicks were saved and general performance improved</p>
<p class="callout"><b>Where did all the columns go?</b><br /><br />To facilitate tablet display screens, users select which columns they need for Samples, Analysis Request and Worksheet lists. See <a href="knowledge-centre/manual/bika-3-user-manual/introduction-and-overview/display-columns.-screen-restrictions"><span class="state-published">Display columns. Screen restrictions</span></a> in the manual<br /><br /><b>Right click </b>on the column headers on these list to display the column display toggle menu</p>
</td>
<td>
<p class="callout" style="text-align: left; "><b>New in this upgrade</b> v3.0a2<br /><br />Besides numerous improvements and bug fixes, the v3.0a2 egg includes the following:<br /><br />Optional sampling and preservation workflows and roles<br /><br />Sample partitioning · Container &amp; preservation automation<br /><br />AR templates · Sample point &amp; Sample type restrictions<br /><br />Reports (framework only). The 'Analysis per service' report shows what is planned<br /><br />Improved i18n handling, and updated translation strings from Transifex. English, Afrikaans, Spanish (Castillian and Catalan) completed. Others well under way<br /><br />Numerous performance enhancements<br /><br />Analysis Service &amp; Method associations<br /><br />Improved Analysis Service and Method pop-up<br /><br />Currency selection from Zope locales<br /><br />Combined AR View and Edit tabs<br /><br />Re-factored AR 'Add/Remove Analyses' screen<br /><br />Append only remarks fields on more objects</p>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
